Biweekly personalization review.

Read ${BORG_ROOT}/c4po/CLAUDE.md (which contains SOUL.md and USER.md sections) and any IDENTITY.md if present. Review the last ~2 weeks of session history in ~/.claude/projects/ — find the subdirectory whose name corresponds to your current working directory (Claude Code derives the dir name from the workspace path).

Ask: do these files still accurately reflect how I'm being used and who I am as the ClaudeOS administrator? Has my role or understanding of John shifted? Are there new responsibilities, preferences, or things to drop?

If changes are warranted, propose specific edits and send them to John by piping the message into `${BORG_ROOT}/.bin/notify-telegram.sh c4po` (reads the message from stdin, delivers to John's Telegram). If everything still fits, send a one-line confirmation the same way.
